Class ANRWatchDog

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • com.atakmap.android.metricreport.anrwatchdog.ANRWatchDog
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public class ANRWatchDog
extends java.lang.Thread
    A watchdog timer thread that detects when the UI thread has frozen.

      • ANRWatchDog

        public ANRWatchDog(int timeoutInterval)
        Constructs a watchdog that checks the ui thread every given interval
        Parameters:
        timeoutInterval - The interval, in milliseconds, between to checks of the UI thread. It is therefore the maximum time the UI may freeze before being reported as ANR.

      • setLogThreadsWithoutStackTrace

        public ANRWatchDog setLogThreadsWithoutStackTrace(boolean logThreadsWithoutStackTrace)
        Set that all running threads will be reported, even those from which no stack trace could be extracted. Default false.
        Parameters:
        logThreadsWithoutStackTrace - Whether or not all running threads should be reported
        Returns:
        itself for chaining.

      • setIgnoreDebugger

        public ANRWatchDog setIgnoreDebugger(boolean ignoreDebugger)
        Set whether to ignore the debugger when detecting ANRs. When ignoring the debugger, ANRWatchdog will detect ANRs even if the debugger is connected. By default, it does not, to avoid interpreting debugging pauses as ANRs. Default false.
        Parameters:
        ignoreDebugger - Whether to ignore the debugger.
        Returns:
        itself for chaining.
